![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/570bb46b-b0fa-4f33-b926-2076b77cb69e/Messenger_creation_2872836856230861.jpeg?format=original)

CM Punk opens the show furious. He calls out the Rock for walking into the WWE and pretending that he cares about this business.

Punk says he has never been so desperate as to wear a fake title and call himself the people's champion, he earns his titles.

Punk says he's never been so desperate as to SELL HIS SOUL the way John Cena did. John Cena STOLE something from CM Punk. After 20 years, everyone can see what CM Punk has seen all along, that John Cena has been selling these people bullshit.

Mr. Never Give Up has ironically given up on himself. CM Punk will get his hands on both of those bald freaks down the line. But it's time for little brother Seth Rollins.

Punk says Becky Lynch better come get Seth Rollins but Rollins music hits and the brawl immediately begins and doesn't end until dozens of security guards can get out there. But Punk and Rollins break free from their grasp multiple times.

They brawl for about five minutes before we go to commercials

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/ea4ccac1-47c2-4f5d-8cca-38c802610dc1/Messenger_creation_1343686583440272.jpeg?format=original)

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/458e7a2e-d7d2-4883-9206-6ef3f2dbc488/Messenger_creation_613182001472007.jpeg?format=original)

Gunther says Otis is just like Jey Uso, a people pleaser who makes a fool of himself to entertain the audience. He doesn't belong in the sacred ring.

Does Otis even look at himself in the mirror? Gunther does, he sees himself wearing a World Championship belt while Otis can't even find a belt that fits.

What's sad is Otis could be great if he had some respect for himself.

\*BIG BOOT\* Gunther kicks Otis in the face and the match begins.

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/49841de3-927d-480c-94bb-52d8138addbc/Messenger_creation_1393890215352442.jpeg?format=original)

*   ## **_GUNTHER DEF. OTIS_**
    

Very good Heavyweight wrestling match. Very stiff. Everything connected and looked real.

Post match, Gunther tries to attack Otis and Tozawa but Jey USO gets involved. Grayson Waller and Austin Theory attack Jey USO but Jey takes them both out and Gunther chokes out Jey after the distraction

